<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - CAB: 5000, 9100, 9200, 9300, 9400 - REMOVE AND INSTALL -
        DOOR LOCK ASSEMBLY
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="2">
        <title>DOOR LOCK ASSEMBLY</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <para>The door locks and the console-mounted key switch are coded differently so that two separate keys
                operate the ignition switch and door locks. The code number is stamped on the key switch body just in
                back of the cap nut. The code number does not appear on the door lock assembly.
            </para>
            <para>To REPLACE the door lock, you must replace the complete assembly. The tumbler unit is not removable.
                If you must replace one door lock, replace both of them with matching locks.
            </para>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Remove</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the lower door cover panel. Refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s16005v_30.xml" xrefid="x1600508">CAB DOOR GLASS, Remove</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the rod end clip (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1600564">Item 1, Figure 64</hotlnk>) and detach the lock control rod (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1600564">Item 2, Figure 64</hotlnk>) from the door lock assembly.
                </para>
                <figure id="f1600564" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../figg16/G1600556.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                             resolution="72"/>
                    <caption>Figure 64. Disconnecting Lock Control Rod</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. ROD END CLIP</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. LOCK CONTROL ROD</callout1>
                        <callout1>3. DOOR LATCH CONTROL ROD</callout1>
                        <callout1>4. OUTER DOOR HANDLE</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1600565">Figure 65</hotlnk>
                for Items in parentheses.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1600565" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg16/G1600557.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 65. Removing Door Lock Retainer Clip</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. LOCK CYLINDER RETAINER CLIP</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. LOCK CONTROL ROD</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. HEX NUT WITH WASHER</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. DOOR</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. OUTER DOOR HANDLE ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                    <callout1>6. ROD END CLIP</callout1>
                    <callout1>7. DOOR LOCK CYLINDER ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Pull the retainer clip (Item 1) from the lock assembly (Item 7).</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Rotate the lock assembly (Item 7) slightly, then remove it from the door (Item 4).
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Install</title>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1600565">Figure 65</hotlnk>
                for Items in parentheses.
            </para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Put the lock cylinder assembly (Item 7) into place, and fasten it with the retainer clip
                    (Item 1).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Attach the lock control rod (Item 2) to the door lock assembly (Item 7) with the rod end
                    clip (Item 6).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Replace the lower door cover panel. Refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s16005v_30.xml" xrefid="x1600509">CAB DOOR GLASS, Install
                        <xref refid="x1600509"/>
                    </hotlnk>
                    .
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
